Date:  2/11/1839
Source:  Robert Maunsell
Author:  WILY & MAUNSELL
Vol / Page:  61
Edition:  1938
Quote:   ... and the tribe will often deem it to be due to his rank to bring `a fight' as they call it, against him, and as a demonstration of regard, strip him of all the property they may find about him.
